% Energy rebound is a phenomenon whereby 
% some expected energy savings fail to materialize 
% after an energy efficiency upgrade (EEU)
% due to behavior changes and economic effects.
% If large rebound exists, energy efficiency 
% may be less effective than supposed to  
% reduce energy consumption and carbon emissions, and 
% Paris objectives may be at risk.
% For accurate analysis of the size of rebound from any EEU, 
% rebound frameworks should be comprehensive, 
