Bringing together the high stakes of energy efficiency 
\emph{vis-\`{a}-vis} emissions reduction goals
and the desirable characteristics of rebound frameworks discussed above,
we see that comprehensive rebound frameworks are needed for 
developing energy efficiency policy to meet emissions targets. 
Effective policy should be informed by rebound analyses conducted within
a comprehensive rebound framework with firm theoretical foundations.

In fact, several scholars have developed previous rebound analysis frameworks.
